					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13030130#post-4857001</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13030130/scp-5445#post-4857001</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 30 Dec 2020 01:47:57 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Gaffsey</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6590029</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I've been mulling over the lack of &quot;articles that involve non-Western cultures where the focus of the article isn't 'behold, it's [thing, either perceived or real that is particular to the specific non-Western culture], but now it's anomalous and also sarkic&quot; and this fits the bill (heh) quite nicely. Not a million percent onboard with everyone's favorite imperialist sea snail being involved, but screw it - it's a punchy article, bizarre concept, and well-excecuted. Easy +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
