					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13030130#post-4496253</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13030130/scp-5445#post-4496253</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 10 Feb 2020 20:48:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>NatVoltaic</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2800867</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>&quot;SCP-5445 is a bacterial infection transmissible between humans and restaurants&quot; is a wonderfully bizarre opening line with a very unique direction taken for it. I do feel like this article would work better if it angled into the weirdness of the scenario harder, though the idea of people ordering the skulls without memetic compulsion is enough to win me over. Hesitant +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
